She stands accused of trying to have her husband Austin killed last year. She was arrested and one of her bail conditions included not making contact with him.She applied to have her bail conditions amended because the couple wants to work on their marriage. But this was denied on Thursday.Magistrate Goolam Bawa made it clear that she has not been barred from seeing their children. But he reminded that Austin is ''a state witness'' and therefore she cannot have access to him.Bawa went on to say that her husband will in all likelihood testify about their relationship.She will return to court on June 2. Bawa said the State had ''concluded their investigation'' and the case will be transferred to the High Court in Cape Town.- TMG Digital/TimesLIVE